Full Product Description: Product Details    Allen Bradley MicroLogix Accessories     Allen Bradley offer a range of accessories and parts which are suitable for use with the MicroLogix family of PLCs, giving you full protection and a control system which is customised to meet your requirements. The MicroLogix controllers offer increased application coverage and superior network communications to keep your automated machine processes running smoothly.         2080-USBADAPTER – Adapter Plug for Micro810 PLC     Enable fast, easy PLC programming with the 2080-USBADAPTER by Allen Bradley.  The 2080-USBADAPTER is a USB Adapter Plug designed specifically for use with the Micro810 12-pt PLC. This device is required to connect to a PC for programming. The operating temperature for this adapter is -20 to 55 °C (-4 to 131 °F). It uses a USB Type A-B Male-Male connector.  The Micro810 smart relay micro programmable controller series is ideal for small applications, including temperature control, compressor control, and elevator control. It is the smallest PLC of the Micro800 family and can be conveniently personalised with plug-in modules to meet your specific needs. This cost-effective control solution features high current relay outputs (8A) which replace the need for external relays. The smart relay function blocks can be easily configured by the 1.5 LCD Display and Keypad. Programming is simple to do via the Connected Components Workbench software, which is free to download.              Features and Benefits:     USB adapter plug for the Micro810 12-pt PLC  Snaps easily into the USB port on the control unit  Enables programming with the Connected Components Workbench software  Note: USB cable should not exceed 3m.              What is a PLC?     Programmable Logic Controllers (PLC) are complex computers which automate control processes by using programs to communicate electronic signals to machines and devices. In simplified terms, they are usually comprised of three components:A CPU (Central Processing Unit), which is the brain or processor of the system, Inputs, and Outputs. An input module detects signals from things like switches, sensors, and buttons. This is processed by the CPU, which leads to an output relaying the CPUs instructions to a machine or device. PLC system functions can be expanded by adding extra I/O modules. These devices are widely used in modern industrial automation for controlling machinery, in industries such as packaging, food and beverage production, pharmaceutical, and printing. Allen Bradley PLC systems provide dependable and flexible control capabilities at a fair price to give you seamless performance.

Full Product Description: Product Details    Communications Modules     EtherNet - The 22-COMM-E EtherNet/IP adapter provides an internal EtherNet/IP connection for PowerFlex 40 drives. The adapter allows the drive to be controlled, configured, and data to be collected via an EtherNet/IP network. Web services are also provided and pages can be viewed with standard web browsers. The adapter also supports "Multi-Drive", a unique feature to Allen-Bradley. Multi-Drive allows up to five PowerFlex component class drives to connect to a single node on EtherNet/IP. Benefits include reduced hardware costs and a means to connect PowerFlex 4 drives to EtherNet/IP.  User configurable process display window  TCP/IP configuration (monitor only)  Email notification on fault, fault clear, and/or when the adapter takes its comm or idle fault actions  Monitoring device information, diagnostics and event queue  Direct launching of DriveExplorer or DriveExecutive on user's PC to connect on-line over EtherNet  DeviceNet - The PowerFlex 40 (not the PowerFlex 4) can be integrated with Allen-Bradley PLC Architectures using this optional DeviceNet communications module.  Network - The PowerFlex 70 can be integrated with PLC Architectures using these communications modules which fit neatly inside the PowerFlex 70.         Note    A comms option cover is also needed for EtherNet & DeviceNet modules – choose the cover to match the PowerFlex 40 frame size (B or C).         Allen Bradley Communication Module, 86mm Length, 19mm Depth - 22-COMM-E     Conveniently monitor industrial motor control systems with this communication adapter from Rockwell Automation's Allen Bradley range. It lets you collect, control and configure data on your PC (personal computer) over an ethernet or IP (internet protocol) network. The unit is internally mounted to a PowerFlex 40 AC drive to save space on a control panel. Its unique multi-drive feature lets you connect up to five PowerFlex drives to a single ethernet or IP node, which reduces hardware costs and helps simplify your communication system.         Features and Benefits     User-friendly configurable process-display window lets you choose your preferred view  Conveniently receive fault reports and other diagnostic information by email  Can be quickly and easily installed in the field  Configurable switches for enabling and disabling web pages and setting single or multi-drive modes              Standards and Certifications     UL508C (Underwriters' Laboratories)  CSA(Canadian Standards Authority)  CE (Conformitè Europëenne)  EN (European Norm)              What data can be sent and received by the adapter?     This device is able to transfer time-critical data that's necessary for controlling the PowerFlex drive, such as logic commands and status information, as well as feedback reports.

Item Name: ABB PSE30-600-70 30 A Soft Starter PSR Series IP00 IP20 11 kW
Full Product Description: The softstarter PSE30-600-70 has a rated maximum operational current of 30 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is between 100...250 V AC at 50/60 Hz. PSE features a two-phase control with a soft start and stop through a voltage or a torque ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN, TOR, and Event signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The PSE has functions such as current limit, kickstart, analog output, EOL, underload, and locked rotor protection. To interact with PSE, it has an Illuminated display that uses symbols to become language neutral. As an option, you can add an identical external keypad with a rating of IP66. There are three ways to communicate with PSE. It can be done by hardwire inputs Start/Stop or by Reset of fault. Another popular option is the built-in fieldbus communication Modbus RTU. You can also use an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. PSE is a true general purpose softstarter. It’s a perfect balance between high starting capacity and cost efficiency. Very suitable for small to medium-sized three-phase motors with nominal currents from 18...370 A. Typical applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.
Product Category: Automation >  Automation Surplus >  Soft Start >  Soft Starters

Item Name: ABB PSR12-600-11 Softstarter PSR12-600-81 Compact 600V / 24VDC 11A PSR Series
Full Product Description: The softstarter PSR12-600-11 has a rated maximum operational current of 12 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is 24 V AC/DC. PSR features a two-phase control soft start and stop through a voltage ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The start/stop ramp and time is easy to set by three potentiometers on the front. PSR is often used in combination with a manual motor starter (MMS) from ABB, so mechanical connection kits are available. Another popular option is Fieldbus communication, which can be enabled by an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. The PSR range is our most compact softstarters with basic functionality and values. They are suitable for small three-phase motors with nominal currents from 3...105 A and can manage up to 100 starts per hour. Common applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.

Item Name: ABB PSE85-600-70 85 A Soft Starter PSR Series IP00 IP20 37 kW
Full Product Description: The softstarter PSE85-600-70 has a rated maximum operational current of 85 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is between 100...250 V AC at 50/60 Hz. PSE features a two-phase control with a soft start and stop through a voltage or a torque ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN, TOR, and Event signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The PSE has functions such as current limit, kickstart, analog output, EOL, underload, and locked rotor protection. To interact with PSE, it has an Illuminated display that uses symbols to become language neutral. As an option, you can add an identical external keypad with a rating of IP66. There are three ways to communicate with PSE. It can be done by hardwire inputs Start/Stop or by Reset of fault. Another popular option is the built-in fieldbus communication Modbus RTU. You can also use an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. PSE is a true general purpose softstarter. It’s a perfect balance between high starting capacity and cost efficiency. Very suitable for small to medium-sized three-phase motors with nominal currents from 18...370 A. Typical applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.
Product Category: Automation >  Automation Surplus >  Soft Start >  Soft Starters

Full Product Description: The softstarter PSR37-600-70 has a rated maximum operational current of 37 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is between 100...240 V AC at 50/60 Hz. PSR features a two-phase control soft start and stop through a voltage ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN and a TOR signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The start/stop ramp and time is easy to set by three potentiometers on the front. PSR is often used in combination with a manual motor starter (MMS) from ABB, so mechanical connection kits are available. Another popular option is Fieldbus communication, which can be enabled by an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. The PSR range is our most compact softstarters with basic functionality and values. They are suitable for small three-phase motors with nominal currents from 3...105 A and can manage up to 100 starts per hour. Common applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.
Product Category: Automation >  Automation Surplus >  Soft Start >  Soft Starters

Item Name: ABB PSE45-600-70 45 A Soft Starter PSR Series IP00 IP20 18.5 kW
Full Product Description: The softstarter PSE45-600-70 has a rated maximum operational current of 45 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is between 100...250 V AC at 50/60 Hz. PSE features a two-phase control with a soft start and stop through a voltage or a torque ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN, TOR, and Event signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The PSE has functions such as current limit, kickstart, analog output, EOL, underload, and locked rotor protection. To interact with PSE, it has an Illuminated display that uses symbols to become language neutral. As an option, you can add an identical external keypad with a rating of IP66. There are three ways to communicate with PSE. It can be done by hardwire inputs Start/Stop or by Reset of fault. Another popular option is the built-in fieldbus communication Modbus RTU. You can also use an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. PSE is a true general purpose softstarter. It’s a perfect balance between high starting capacity and cost efficiency. Very suitable for small to medium-sized three-phase motors with nominal currents from 18...370 A. Typical applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.
Product Category: Automation >  Automation Surplus >  Soft Start >  Soft Starters

Engineered for reliability and precision, this sensor detects the presence of objects without direct contact, making it ideal for detecting non-metallic materials such as liquids and bulk solids. ## Key Features • **Sensing Range**: Detects objects up to 40 mm away, providing flexibility for various application needs. • **Output Type**: Features a PNP output with a switching capacity of 200 mA, ensuring robust performance in demanding environments. • **Construction**: Encased in a durable plastic housing with an IP67 rating, ensuring protection against dust and moisture. • **Operating Temperature**: Functions effectively within a temperature range of -25°C to +70°C, making it suitable for diverse industrial conditions. • **Voltage Rating**: Operates on a wide voltage range of 10 to 30 VDC, compatible with various control systems. ## Applications • **Manufacturing**: Ideal for detecting the presence of materials in production lines, enhancing automation efficiency. • **Food and Beverage Industry**: Suitable for applications requiring non-contact detection of liquids and powders, ensuring compliance with hygiene standards. • **Logistics and Warehousing**: Used in conveyor systems for object detection and monitoring, improving workflow and reducing manual handling. • **Plastic and Wood Industries**: Effective in detecting non-metallic objects, optimizing material handling processes. ## Benefits • **Increased Efficiency**: Non-contact sensing reduces wear and tear on equipment, prolonging sensor life and minimizing maintenance costs. • **Enhanced Safety**: By eliminating physical contact, the sensor contributes to a safer operational environment, reducing the risk of accidents. • **Versatile Compatibility**: The sensor’s broad voltage range and output type make it adaptable to various control systems and industrial environments. • **Reliable Performance**: With a robust design and high ingress protection, this sensor ensures consistent performance even in harsh conditions. --- *Product information compiled with AI assistance for reference purposes.*

Full Product Description: The softstarter PSR105-600-70 has a rated maximum operational current of 105 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is between 100...240 V AC at 50/60 Hz. PSR features a two-phase control soft start and stop through a voltage ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN and a TOR signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The start/stop ramp and time is easy to set by three potentiometers on the front. PSR is often used in combination with a manual motor starter (MMS) from ABB, so mechanical connection kits are available. Another popular option is Fieldbus communication, which can be enabled by an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. The PSR range is our most compact softstarters with basic functionality and values. They are suitable for small three-phase motors with nominal currents from 3...105 A and can manage up to 100 starts per hour. Common applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.
Product Category: Automation >  Automation Surplus >  Soft Start >  Soft Starters

Full Product Description: Product Details    Allen Bradley Guardmaster GuardShield 440L Type 4 Finger Protection Safety Light Curtains     Ensure sophisticated presence sensing for your machine safety application with the GuardShield 440L Finger Protection Safety Light Curtains and accessories by Allen Bradley Guardmaster.  The GuardShield family of safety light curtains are general-purpose devices for presence sensing. They can be used on hazardous machinery to ensure perimeter and access detection and point of operation detection, helping to prevent injury to personnel. Point of Operation Control light curtains (POC) are used specifically for finger, hand and arm recognition and should be placed close to the hazard where personnel interact with the machine. This type of safety system uses a transmitter which emits sequential pulses of infrared light to a receiver. When the beams are interrupted a stop signal is immediately sent to the machine.  These GuardShield Light Curtains are self-contained two-box Type 4 Electro Sensitive Protective equipment (ESPE). They have convenient DIP switch selectable Modes of Operation, located beneath a security door in the end caps, which offer advanced features such as:  Fixed blanking (teachable)  Floating blanking (one or two beam)  Beam coding  Start/restart interlock  External device monitoring (EDM)         Features and Benefits:     14mm resolution (finger detection)  Two safety solid state and one auxillary non-safety outputs  Easy maintenance with the Quick Disconnect cables (4-pin for the sender, 8-pin for the receiver)              Applications:     Robot cells  Conveyors  Presses  Forming Operations  Electronic Fences  Workstations  Note: Installation and operation of this safety device must be in strict accordance with accompanying operating instructions.  When ordering both a sender and receiver are included. In addition, a sender cable and a receiver cable will be required. For suitable safety relays, see the "Minotaur" range of products (e.g 447-5587)  Standards: IEC/EN61496 parts 1 & 2, Type 4 ESPE and EN954-1 Cat 4, UL61496, UL1998  Approvals: TUV and CE marked; UL61496, UL1998                   Light Curtain

It's placed between a power supply and a motor to regulate the current before it's used and ensure it's safe for the attached machinery. Full Product Description: The softstarter PSR30-600-70 has a rated maximum operational current of 30 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is between 100...240 V AC at 50/60 Hz. PSR features a two-phase control soft start and stop through a voltage ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN and a TOR signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The start/stop ramp and time is easy to set by three potentiometers on the front. PSR is often used in combination with a manual motor starter (MMS) from ABB, so mechanical connection kits are available. Another popular option is Fieldbus communication, which can be enabled by an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. The PSR range is our most compact softstarters with basic functionality and values. They are suitable for small three-phase motors with nominal currents from 3...105 A and can manage up to 100 starts per hour. Common applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.

Full Product Description: Product Details Allen Bradley SLC500 CPU, PSU and I/O Chassis Enhance flexibility in your control system configuration with the SLC500 Chassis for CPU, PSU and I/O modules by Allen Bradley. This chassis securely houses the processor and I/O modules and comes in four available sizes to meet your application requirements. The modules can be placed in any position and slide easily into slots for optimal convenience and ease of use. Up to 3 chassis can be interconnected, up to a maximum of 30 slots, allowing you to maximise the capabilities of your control system. Allen Bradley provide a range of high-quality, affordable components to help you design a control system that can meet your specific application requirements. With the Allen Bradley SLC 500 and PLC systems you can greatly improve the efficiency and reliability of your automated machine processes and experience peace-of-mind. 4, 7, 10 and 13 slot options Height 171mm, Depth 145mm; Width tabled below What is SLC500? The Allen Bradley SLC500 is a small chassis-based family of programmable controllers, discrete, analogue, and speciality I/O, and peripheral devices. The SLC500 family delivers power and flexibility with a wide range of communication configurations, features, and memory options. The smaller size of the SLC means that it can be used in applications which do not require the larger size and overhead of a traditional, full-size programmable logic controller. Programmable Logic Controllers (PLC) are complex computers which automate control processes by using programs to communicate electronic signals to machines and devices. In simplified terms, they are usually comprised of three components:A CPU (Central Processing Unit), which is the brain or processor of the system, Inputs, and Outputs. An input module detects signals from things like switches, sensors, and buttons. This is processed by the CPU, which leads to an output relaying the CPUs instructions to a machine or device. PLC system functions can be expanded by adding extra I/O modules. PLC systems are widely used in modern industrial automation for controlling machinery, in industries such as packaging, food and beverage production, pharmaceutical, and printing. Allen Bradley offer excellent control capabilities with their flexible SLC/PLC systems to give you optimal power and performance.

Full Product Description: The softstarter PSR12-600-70 has a rated maximum operational current of 12 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is between 100...240 V AC at 50/60 Hz. PSR features a two-phase control soft start and stop through a voltage ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The start/stop ramp and time is easy to set by three potentiometers on the front. PSR is often used in combination with a manual motor starter (MMS) from ABB, so mechanical connection kits are available. Another popular option is Fieldbus communication, which can be enabled by an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. The PSR range is our most compact softstarters with basic functionality and values. They are suitable for small three-phase motors with nominal currents from 3...105 A and can manage up to 100 starts per hour. Common applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.

Full Product Description: Product Details Allen Bradley MicroLogix Accessories Allen Bradley offer a range of accessories and parts which are suitable for use with the MicroLogix family of PLCs, giving you full protection and a control system which is customised to meet your requirements. The MicroLogix controllers offer increased application coverage and superior network communications to keep your automated machine processes running smoothly. 2080-SERIALISOL Isolated Serial Port Plug-in Module The 2080-SERIALISOL unit is an RS232/485 isolated serial port plug-in module for the Micro800 family of programmable logic controllers. It has an isolated voltage of 500 V ac. Mounting torque is 0.2 Nm (1.48 lb-in). The operating temperature range for this unit is -20 to 65 °C (-4 to 149 °F). Dimensions: 62mm x 31.5mm x 20mm Features and Benefits: Compatible with Micro830 Adds further serial communications with Modbus RTU and ASCII protocols for more intensive serial communications tasks Isolated for increased noise immunity Easy installation into the controller by snapping into the module bay and tightening the tapping screw using a screwdriver Up to 5 extra serial ports can be added The MicroLogix family of Programmable Logic Controllers offers excellent control capabilities at a fair price. They can handle a wide range of application types and come in conveniently small sizes to accommodate tight spaces. These handy control units provide superior application coverage with improved network communications. What is a PLC? Programmable Logic Controllers (PLC) are complex computers which automate control processes by using programs to communicate electronic signals to machines and devices. In simplified terms, they are usually comprised of three components:A CPU (Central Processing Unit), which is the brain or processor of the system, Inputs, and Outputs. An input module detects signals from things like switches, sensors, and buttons. This is processed by the CPU, which leads to an output relaying the CPUs instructions to a machine or device. Logic Controller system functions can be expanded by adding extra I/O modules. These devices are widely used in modern industrial automation for controlling machinery, in industries such as packaging, food and beverage production, pharmaceutical, and printing.

Full Product Description: The softstarter PSR9-600-11 has a rated maximum operational current of 9 A with an operating voltage span from 208...600 V AC. The rated control voltage is 24 V AC/DC. PSR features a two-phase control soft start and stop through a voltage ramp. It has built-in bypass for easy installation and energy saving. A RUN signal is available from a relay output in NO (normally open state). The start/stop ramp and time is easy to set by three potentiometers on the front. PSR is often used in combination with a manual motor starter (MMS) from ABB, so mechanical connection kits are available. Another popular option is Fieldbus communication, which can be enabled by an external adaptor and a Fieldbus plug. The PSR range is our most compact softstarters with basic functionality and values. They are suitable for small three-phase motors with nominal currents from 3...105 A and can manage up to 100 starts per hour. Common applications are, for example, pumps, fans, compressors, and conveyors.

Full Product Description: Product Details Allen Bradley MicroLogix Accessories Allen Bradley offer a range of accessories and parts which are suitable for use with the MicroLogix family of PLCs, giving you full protection and a control system which is customised to meet your requirements. The MicroLogix controllers offer increased application coverage and superior network communications to keep your automated machine processes running smoothly. Allen Bradley LCD Display Module For Use With Micro810 Series Controllers - Micro800 Series - 2080-LCD Enhance monitoring, diagnosis and configuration of your programmable logic controllers (PLCs) with this multi-purpose display module from Rockwell Automation's Allen Bradley range. It's designed specifically for controllers in the Micro 800 and 810 series and lets you manipulate these devices without the need for software. The unit has a liquid crystal display (LCD) screen that offers a visual representation of values and settings, making configuration easier. As an added advantage, you can use this display module as a backup memory module for temporary configuration storage. Wide operating temperature range of -20°C to +55°C for use in demanding environments IP20 (ingress protection) rated to resist dust and objects larger than 12mm in size Soft buttons for non-slip use Standards and Certifications UL (Underwriters' Laboratory) CE (Conformitè Europëenne) RoHS (Restriction of Hazardous Substances) What maintenance does this display module need? Allows simplified monitoring and modification of application data Snaps easily into the LCD module bay Can configure and operate smart relay function blocks Acts as a backup memory module for Micro810 controllers for extra reliability If used properly, this unit doesn't need much maintenance. You should keep it away from objects with strong magnetic fields to prevent colour distortion. It's also necessary to install it in a dry environment to prevent condensation and possible short circuits. What are PLCs used for? Programmable Logic Controllers (PLC) are used to monitor and automate control processes. These control systems are often used in industrial automation, for example to monitor and control machinery in production lines. Inputs can be triggered via things like switches, sensors, and buttons while outputs send instructions to devices, such as motor starts and relays.

Full Product Description: Product Details    Communications Modules     EtherNet - The 22-COMM-E EtherNet/IP adapter provides an internal EtherNet/IP connection for PowerFlex 40 drives. The adapter allows the drive to be controlled, configured, and data to be collected via an EtherNet/IP network. Web services are also provided and pages can be viewed with standard web browsers. The adapter also supports "Multi-Drive", a unique feature to Allen-Bradley. Multi-Drive allows up to five PowerFlex component class drives to connect to a single node on EtherNet/IP. Benefits include reduced hardware costs and a means to connect PowerFlex 4 drives to EtherNet/IP.  User configurable process display window  TCP/IP configuration (monitor only)  Email notification on fault, fault clear, and/or when the adapter takes its comm or idle fault actions  Monitoring device information, diagnostics and event queue  Direct launching of DriveExplorer or DriveExecutive on user's PC to connect on-line over EtherNet  DeviceNet - The PowerFlex 40 (not the PowerFlex 4) can be integrated with Allen-Bradley PLC Architectures using this optional DeviceNet communications module.  Network - The PowerFlex 70 can be integrated with PLC Architectures using these communications modules which fit neatly inside the PowerFlex 70.         Note    A comms option cover is also needed for EtherNet & DeviceNet modules – choose the cover to match the PowerFlex 40 frame size (B or C).         Allen Bradley Adapter For Use With PowerFlex Series, 19mm Length, 78.5mm Depth - 20-COMM-D     This adapter from Rockwell Automation's Allen Bradley range is an embedded communication tool designed for use with drives in the PowerFlex series. It enables easy control of your drives and also serves as a channel for data collection. Its compact dimensions of 19 (length) and 78.5mm (depth) make it suitable for small spaces. This device's switches let you set a node address and network data rate before powering the drive to eliminate the need for external configuration software. The unit also comes with captive screws that secure it to the drive, so it won't fall off when used with vibrating systems.  Compatible with DeviceNet and DriveExplorer software for quick and easy interfacing with computersLight-emitting diode (LED) status indicators show operating conditions for easy troubleshootingSupplied with grounding wrist strap for protection from electrostatic discharge (ESD)         Standards and Certifications     ANSI (American National Standards Institute)BS EN (British Standard European Norm)              What tools do I need to install this adapter?     In order to install this adapter, you'll need a flat screwdriver, a DeviceNet cable, configuration software and a computer with a DeviceNet communications adapter installed.

Full Product Description: Product Details    SLC500 Modular PLC CPUs     The Allen-Bradley SLC 500 is a small chassis-based family of programmable controllers, discrete, analogue, and speciality I/O, and peripheral devices. The SLC 500 family delivers power and flexibility with a wide range of communication configurations, features, and memory options. The RSLogix 500 ladder logic programming package provides flexible editors, point-and-click I/O configuration, and a powerful database editor, as well as diagnostic and troubleshooting tools to help you save project development time and maximize productivity.    With up to 64 K of configurable data/program memory available and over 60 types of I/O modules, as well as a choice of networking options, the SLC system provides a powerful solution for stand-alone or distributed industrial control.         Features and Benefits of SLC500 series:     Powerful, yet affordable – SLC 500 programmable controllers provide excellent value with extensive capabilities to address a broad range of applications including material handling, HVAC control, high-speed assembly operations, small process control, simple motion control, and SCADA.  Modularity – Modular processes, power supplies, I/O, memory options, and communication interfaces allow for a configurable and expandable system. You can configure your system for the number of I/O, the amount of memory, and the communication networks needed. Later, you can expand the system by adding I/O, memory, or communication interfaces.
